            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Aim for at least 60% unique content per page — with 70%+ being the target for competitive niches. A Moz study found city pages with 70%+ unique content rank 3 to 5 positions higher than template-only pages.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What makes city pages count as doorway pages?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google's rule of thumb: if removing the city name from two pages makes them indistinguishable, the pages are doorways. Add local photos, area-specific pricing, city-specific team assignments, and genuine local knowledge to stay outside the doorway definition.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
